# Section 2 — Pesapal Specifically
# Estimated time: 3 hours
# Checkpoint: answer 2 questions before moving on
# Note: this is a good stopping point after 2 hours
#       if tired — split into 2 sessions if needed

Teach me:
- How Pesapal works as a gateway in East Africa
- The difference between Pesapal sandbox and live
  environments and how to switch between them
- What credentials Pesapal gives me and what each one does
  (consumer key, consumer secret, access token)
- How Pesapal's OAuth token system works — why I need
  to request a token before every API call
- The key Pesapal API endpoints I will use:
    - Get OAuth token
    - Submit order request
    - Register IPN (webhook URL)
    - Query payment status
- What IPN means (Instant Payment Notification) and
  how Pesapal uses it differently from a standard webhook
- How to test payments in sandbox without real money
  (test phone numbers, test amounts)

